[English version]
Call for Papers

Intellectica (http://intellectica.org/) is a referenced French-language
journal devoted to the publication of theoretical, epistemological and
historical work in the field of Cognitive Science. The journal also publishes
articles in English. Founded in 1985, the journal will celebrate its 30th
anniversary in 2015. On this occasion, the new Editorial Committee, which will
have its seat at the ISCC (Institute of Communication Sciences of CNRS),
wishes in the future to promote volumes of the journal entirely based on
papers that are freely submitted; these volumes will supplement the volumes
based on thematic dossiers that the revue has produced in the past (2 volumes/
year) and will continue to produce.
In this perspective, the journal is now making an open Call for Papers.
Details:
•	Deadline for submission of full manuscript: 26 March 2014.
•	Date of publication: December 2014.
•	Language: French or English
•	Format of texts: see “Manuscript submission” on the website of the
journal (http://intellectica.org/en/manuscript-submission/)

  Articles which are submitted after the 26th March will be considered for
publication in a subsequent volume in 2015.
Intellectica wishes to establish itself as a reference journal and a space for
debate by publishing high-quality articles with a reflexive dimension in the
field of Cognitive Science. We hope that the community of research scientists
in this domain will appreciate the work accomplished by the journal, and that
they will contribute to its evolution.
For all questions concerning this call for papers: olivier.gapenne@utc.fr

Olivier Gapenne, Chief Editor




